</div></div>","info":{"doc":"Stream type for Unicode Character Database (UCD) files\n\nUnicode data files are semicolon `;` (U+003B) separated fields, except for\nUnihan files and a few others that are tab (U+0009) separated. White spaces\naround field values are not significant. Line comments are prefixed with a\nnumber sign `#` (U+0023).\n","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic/CharacterDatabase.html#Unicode.UCDStream","kind":"structure","line":9,"name":"Unicode.UCDStream","sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/3b873385fdbca8b43ee1e3310bf282743091a14d/UnicodeBasic/CharacterDatabase.lean#L9-L19"}}],"imports":["Init"],"instances":[{"className":"Inhabited","name":"Unicode.instInhabitedUCDStream","typeNames":["Unicode.UCDStream"]},{"className":"Std.Stream","name":"Unicode.UCDStream.instStreamArraySlice","typeNames":["Unicode.UCDStream","Array"]}],"name":"UnicodeBasic.CharacterDatabase"}